# Mos Lint: Agent Consumption

## Golden rule

**Never pipe `mgate lint` output through Python, awk, or any glue script.** The CLI has built-in flags for every agent use case. If a flag is missing, that's a feature gap — file a bug, don't work around it.

## Quick reference

```bash
# Grouped summary (text, human-readable)
mgate lint --severity error --summary

# Grouped summary with sample diagnostics (text)
mgate lint --severity error --summary -v

# Machine-readable JSON summary with samples
mgate lint --severity error --summary -v --format json

# Full diagnostic list as JSON array
mgate lint --format json

# Only VCS-changed files
mgate lint --changed

# Suppress pre-existing baseline diagnostics
mgate lint --changed --new-only
```

Also accessible as `mos gate lint ...`.

## Exit codes

| Code | Meaning |
|---|---|
| 0 | Clean — no findings |
| 1 | Findings present |
| 2 | Internal linter error |

## JSON summary shape

```json
[
  {
    "severity": "error",
    "rule": "terminal-in-active",
    "count": 52,
    "samples": [
      {
        "file": ".mos/contracts/active/CON-2026-069/contract.mos",
        "message": "...",
        "artifact_id": "CON-2026-069",
        "suggested_action": "Move the artifact with terminal status to archive/"
      }
    ]
  }
]
```

## When you need per-artifact IDs

Use `--format json` (full output) with `jq`, not Python:

```bash
mgate lint --severity error --format json | jq -r '.[] | select(.rule=="terminal-in-active") | .artifact_id'
```

## Check current flags

Flags change. Run `mgate lint --help` at session start if unsure.
